    "Additionally, D(S) provides the operational state of the cooker, denoted as CookerState i, which can be either \"Off\" or \"On\".",
    "Lastly, the current condition of the soup in the cooker is represented by SoupState i, which can take one of the following values: \"Cooking\", \"Cooked\", or \"Not Started\".",
    "Thus, the information for cooker c i is formatted as: \"c i has n i onions.c i is CookerState i.",
    "Soup in c i is SoupState i.",
    "\"Kitchen Counter Information The state description D(S) includes information about kitchen counters, which are primarily used for temporary object storage."
